## Context
The spec describes `make ticket-archive` to move old closed tickets
to `tickets/archive/`. Must preserve the DAG: never archive a
closed ticket referenced by a live ticket's Blocked-by,
X-Discovered-from, or X-Supersedes header.

## Relevant files
- `scripts/validate_tickets.py` — reuse ticket parser from vt
- `scripts/archive_tickets.py` — new script
- `Makefile` — add `ticket-archive` target

## Actions
1. Write `scripts/archive_tickets.py`:
   - Parse all tickets in `tickets/` (not `tickets/archive/`)
   - Collect candidates: Status: closed, last log entry older
     than DAYS threshold (default 90)
   - Collect all Ids referenced by Blocked-by, X-Discovered-from,
     X-Supersedes in non-archived tickets
   - Remove from candidates any ticket whose Id is in the
     referenced set (DAG safety)
   - Print plan: "Will archive N tickets: [ids]. Skipping M
     DAG-referenced: [ids]."
   - With --execute: `git mv` each candidate to `tickets/archive/`,
     then commit
   - Without --execute: dry-run only (default)
2. Add `ticket-archive` target to Makefile with DAYS parameter

## Test
First test: `test_archive_tickets.py`
- Closed ticket older than threshold with no references → archivable
- Closed ticket older than threshold referenced by open ticket → not archivable
- Closed ticket younger than threshold → not archivable
- X-Discovered-from reference also protects from archive

## Verification
- [ ] Dry run lists correct candidates
- [ ] DAG-referenced tickets are excluded
- [ ] `--execute` moves files and commits

## Exit criteria
- `make ticket-archive` does a dry run
- `make ticket-archive EXECUTE=1` performs the archive
- DAG references are always respected
